NEWCASTLE DISEASE, HOBBY BIRDS - ISRAEL (OIE)
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sat, 18 Jun 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Weekly Disease Information,17 Jun 2005, 18, 24 [edited]
<http://oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm#Sec3>

Newcastle disease in Israel
---------------------------
See also: 15 Apr 2005 ["The delegate declares his country free from the
disease"]; 20 May 2005 ["Newcastle disease in Israel in pigeons"].
(Date of previous outbreak of Newcastle disease [NCD] in Israel reported to
the OIE: Feb 2005).
Immediate notification report
--------------------
Information received on 16 Jun 2005 from Dr Moshe Chaimovitz, Director of
Veterinary and Animal Health Services, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural
Development, Beit-Dagan:
Report date: 14 Jun 2005.
Reason for immediate notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease or
infection in a country or zone/compartment.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 3 May 2005.
Date of start of the event: 3 May 2005.
Clinical disease: yes.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, post-mortem and laboratory.
Details of outbreak
-------------
1st administrative division: Petach-Tiqwa district
Type of epidemiological unit: farm
Name of the location: Newe-Yamin
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 May 2005
Species: avi
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
20 / 1 / 1 / 19 / 0
Description of affected population: backyard mixed hobby birds.
Diagnosis
---------
Laboratories where diagnosis was made: Hadera regional poultry disease
laboratory;
Diagnostic tests used:
1. haemagglutination inhibition test;
2. virus isolation by egg inoculation;
3. intracerebral pathogenicity index test (ICPI: 1.83)
Date: 6 Jun 2005;
Results: positive.
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
1. stamping out (8 May 2005);
2. movement control inside the country;
3. screening;
4. vaccination;
5. disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s).
Vaccination in response to the outbreak:
Species/ Total number of vaccinated animals/ Details of the vaccine
1.poultry/ all flocks within a radius of 10 km/ live virus vaccine (VH
strain) by spray
2.pigeons/ all pigeons within a radius of 10 km/ inactivated virus vaccine
(VH strain)
In Israel, NCD vaccination is compulsory. Immediate booster-vaccination
orders were issued to the owners of all poultry holdings and holdings with
other avian species within a radius of 10 km around the outbreak.
Treatment of affected animals: no.
Vaccination prohibited: no.
Other details/comments: all poultry holdings within a radius of 3 km of the
outbreak were checked serologically and/or clinically for Newcastle
disease. There were no indications of infection on any of these farms.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This notification mentions "backyard mixed hobby birds" without further
specification. The previous notification, describing an NCD outbreak in May
2005, mentioned "hobby pigeons". Data on the species involved in the
current outbreak will be helpful. - Mod.TG]
